WEBVTT

00:00:24.083 --> 00:00:26.292
<i>  </i>
<i>One month has passed since this game began.</i>

00:00:26.292 --> 00:00:28.000
"December 2, 2022"       "First Floor: Tolbana"
<i>One month has passed since this game began.</i>

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.333
"December 2, 2022"       "First Floor: Tolbana"
<i>During that time, 2,000 people have died.</i>

00:00:31.375 --> 00:00:35.500
<i>However, no one has yet been</i>
<i>able to clear the first floor.</i>

00:00:37.042 --> 00:00:39.167
<i>I was a beta tester,</i>

00:00:39.167 --> 00:00:41.875
<i>and even I haven't</i>
<i>found the boss room.</i>

00:00:45.250 --> 00:00:49.083
<i>And today, we're finally</i>
<i>holding a meeting</i>

00:00:49.083 --> 00:00:51.417
<i>on how to defeat</i>
<i>the first-floor boss.</i>

00:01:03.417 --> 00:01:07.792
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:08.125 --> 00:01:13.625
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:13.958 --> 00:01:24.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:01:24.958 --> 00:01:29.917
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:01:30.250 --> 00:01:34.625
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:01:34.958 --> 00:01:37.333
<i>Out of control</i>

00:01:37.667 --> 00:01:42.917
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:48.042
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:01:48.375 --> 00:01:54.542
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:01:54.875 --> 00:01:58.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:01:58.958 --> 00:02:03.917
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:04.250 --> 00:02:09.875
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:10.792 --> 00:02:13.250
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:13.583 --> 00:02:18.958
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:02:22.042 --> 00:02:26.042
"Beater"

00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:34.042
Okay, let's get started, people!

00:02:35.750 --> 00:02:39.833
Thank you for responding
to my summons today.

00:02:39.833 --> 00:02:41.250
My name is Diabel.

00:02:41.250 --> 00:02:44.375
My job is... in my own mind,
I like to think I'm a "knight."

00:02:45.250 --> 00:02:47.167
There's no job system
in this game!

00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:47.792
A knight?

00:02:47.792 --> 00:02:49.625
--So is this meeting a joke too?
--You should take this seriously!

00:02:52.208 --> 00:02:54.583
Today, our party discovered

00:02:54.583 --> 00:02:57.167
the boss room at the top
of the tower.

00:02:57.167 --> 00:02:58.500
Seriously?

00:02:59.167 --> 00:03:02.458
We need to defeat the boss,
reach the second floor,

00:03:03.167 --> 00:03:06.875
and tell everyone waiting
in the Town of Beginnings

00:03:06.875 --> 00:03:10.083
that it is possible
to beat this game.

00:03:10.083 --> 00:03:13.500
And that's the duty of every
one of us here now!

00:03:14.083 --> 00:03:15.417
Isn't that right, everybody?

00:03:26.667 --> 00:03:28.250
Okay!

00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:32.167
Then without further delay, I'd like
to get this boss-raid meeting started.

00:03:32.750 --> 00:03:35.375
First, I want you to team
up into parties of six.

00:03:36.667 --> 00:03:37.042
--Of course we'll be in the same party.

00:03:37.042 --> 00:03:39.708
--A conventional party has no chance
against a Floor Boss.
--Of course we'll be in the same party.

00:03:39.708 --> 00:03:40.625
--I'll be the leader.

00:03:40.625 --> 00:03:41.667
--We'll need to form a raid group
--I'll be the leader.

00:03:41.667 --> 00:03:42.625
using multiple parties.

00:03:42.625 --> 00:03:43.625
Let's do this.

00:03:52.958 --> 00:03:54.917
You got left out too?

00:03:55.542 --> 00:03:56.792
I wasn't left out.

00:03:57.125 --> 00:04:01.625
Everyone else seemed to be friends
already, so I just stayed out of it.

00:04:01.625 --> 00:04:04.583
So you're a solo player?
Then want to partner with me?

00:04:06.750 --> 00:04:09.917
He just said we can't beat
the boss on our own.

00:04:09.917 --> 00:04:11.458
So just for this fight?

00:04:19.208 --> 00:04:21.208
"Do you accept party invitation?"

00:04:28.875 --> 00:04:31.625
Okay, are you about done
forming your parties?

00:04:32.208 --> 00:04:32.750
Then--

00:04:32.750 --> 00:04:34.042
Hold up a second!

00:04:41.792 --> 00:04:43.583
My name's Kibaou.

00:04:43.917 --> 00:04:47.375
There's something I wanna say
before we take on the boss.

00:04:48.167 --> 00:04:51.750
Some of you here
need to apologize

00:04:51.750 --> 00:04:54.000
to the 2,000 who
have died so far!

00:04:57.500 --> 00:05:01.292
Kibaou, these people
you're referring to...

00:05:01.292 --> 00:05:04.167
...do you mean the
ex–beta testers, perhaps?

00:05:04.167 --> 00:05:05.667
Of course I do!

00:05:06.208 --> 00:05:10.167
On the day this stupid game started,
the beta guys ditched us beginners,

00:05:10.167 --> 00:05:12.417
and they all disappeared.

00:05:12.417 --> 00:05:14.708
They took all the good hunting spots

00:05:14.708 --> 00:05:17.042
and easy quests for themselves,

00:05:17.042 --> 00:05:19.375
so they were the only
ones getting stronger.

00:05:19.375 --> 00:05:22.375
And since then, they've just
ignored the rest of us.

00:05:23.583 --> 00:05:27.375
There's got to be some of them here!
Guys who were beta testers!

00:05:27.375 --> 00:05:29.625
We should make them get
on their knees and apologize,

00:05:29.625 --> 00:05:33.125
and give up all the items and
money they've hoarded.

00:05:33.125 --> 00:05:36.750
As party members, we can't
trust them with our lives,

00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:37.875
and they can't trust us!

00:05:42.917 --> 00:05:44.125
Can I say something?

00:05:51.125 --> 00:05:53.000
My name is Agil.

00:05:53.417 --> 00:05:56.583
Kibaou, let me get this straight...

00:05:56.583 --> 00:06:01.250
You're saying that because the ex–beta testers
didn't take care of them, many beginners died.

00:06:01.250 --> 00:06:04.708
That they should take responsibility,
apologize, and provide compensation.

00:06:04.708 --> 00:06:05.875
Is that right?

00:06:05.875 --> 00:06:07.583
Y-Yeah.

00:06:09.250 --> 00:06:12.208
You received this guidebook
too, didn't you?

00:06:12.750 --> 00:06:14.875
It was provided for free
at the item store, after all.

00:06:15.292 --> 00:06:16.708
Sure, I got it...

00:06:16.708 --> 00:06:17.708
So what if I did?

00:06:17.917 --> 00:06:21.333
It was the ex–beta testers
who were distributing these.

00:06:21.333 --> 00:06:22.500
Seriously?

00:06:24.792 --> 00:06:25.875
Listen up.

00:06:25.875 --> 00:06:28.375
Everyone had equal access
to this information.

00:06:28.375 --> 00:06:30.417
And yet, many players still died.

00:06:30.958 --> 00:06:32.583
What to learn from
those failures,

00:06:32.583 --> 00:06:35.250
and how to try to
defeat the boss...

00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:38.875
That's what I thought
we'd be discussing here.

00:06:50.917 --> 00:06:52.375
All right.

00:06:52.375 --> 00:06:54.208
Okay, can we resume
the meeting now?

00:06:55.958 --> 00:06:57.625
As for information
on the boss...

00:06:57.625 --> 00:07:01.208
Actually, the latest edition of
that guidebook was just issued.

00:07:02.917 --> 00:07:07.083
According to it, the boss's name
is Illfang the Kobold Lord.

00:07:07.458 --> 00:07:10.958
Also, he has an entourage known
as the Ruin Kobold Sentinels.

00:07:11.625 --> 00:07:14.458
The boss is armed with
an axe and a buckler.

00:07:14.458 --> 00:07:17.875
He has four health bars,
and when the last one is in the red,

00:07:18.375 --> 00:07:21.417
he switches to a curved sword-type
weapon called a Talwar.

00:07:21.417 --> 00:07:24.042
His attack pattern changes too.

00:07:24.792 --> 00:07:27.333
Wow...

00:07:27.333 --> 00:07:31.125
Amazing.

00:07:31.125 --> 00:07:32.542
This concludes the briefing.

00:07:33.250 --> 00:07:38.000
Lastly, regarding item distribution,
money will be automatically divided equally.

00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:41.375
EXP goes to the party
that defeats the monster.

00:07:41.375 --> 00:07:43.833
And whoever receives
an item keeps it.

00:07:44.500 --> 00:07:45.500
Any objections?

00:07:49.542 --> 00:07:52.667
Okay, we leave tomorrow,
at 10 in the morning.

00:07:53.458 --> 00:07:54.500
All right... dismissed!

00:08:30.708 --> 00:08:32.792
Those are pretty tasty, aren't they?

00:08:34.250 --> 00:08:35.708
Mind if I sit down?

00:08:47.375 --> 00:08:49.292
Do you really think it's good?

00:08:49.292 --> 00:08:50.375
Of course.

00:08:51.417 --> 00:08:54.875
Ever since I came to this town,
I've been eating at least one daily.

00:08:54.875 --> 00:08:57.292
I do change it up a little though.

00:08:57.708 --> 00:08:58.708
Change it up?

00:09:00.833 --> 00:09:02.625
Try putting some on the bread.

00:09:13.542 --> 00:09:14.875
Cream?

00:09:37.958 --> 00:09:40.125
It's the reward for a quest called

00:09:40.125 --> 00:09:42.625
"The Heifer Strikes Back,"
one village behind us.

00:09:43.375 --> 00:09:45.292
If you want to do it,
I'll tell you the trick.

00:09:46.708 --> 00:09:51.042
I didn't come to this town
to eat good food.

00:09:51.708 --> 00:09:53.625
Then why did you?

00:09:54.583 --> 00:09:56.792
So I can still be me.

00:09:57.542 --> 00:09:59.958
I'd rather stay myself until
the very last moment

00:09:59.958 --> 00:10:04.833
than lock myself inside an inn back
in the first town, and slowly rot away.

00:10:07.042 --> 00:10:09.292
Even if I'm defeated by
a monster and die,

00:10:09.792 --> 00:10:13.958
I don't want to lose to
this game... to this world.

00:10:13.958 --> 00:10:14.958
No matter what.

00:10:20.792 --> 00:10:23.375
I wouldn't want a party
member dying on me...

00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:26.250
So at the very least,
don't die tomorrow.

00:10:31.625 --> 00:10:32.250
"December 3, 2022"       "Floor 1: Forest Field"

00:10:32.250 --> 00:10:34.208
"December 3, 2022"       "Floor 1: Forest Field"
Let's go over it again.

00:10:34.208 --> 00:10:36.083
As the leftover team,

00:10:36.083 --> 00:10:40.000
our target is the Ruin Kobold
Sentinels, the boss's entourage.

00:10:40.458 --> 00:10:41.750
I know.

00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:45.708
I'll use a sword skill to
knock their poleaxes up.

00:10:45.708 --> 00:10:47.875
The second I do,
switch and jump in.

00:10:48.500 --> 00:10:49.750
Switch?

00:10:50.625 --> 00:10:54.500
Don't tell me... Is this the first time
you've ever been in a party?

00:10:54.667 --> 00:10:55.667
Yes.

00:11:11.042 --> 00:11:12.250
Listen up, everyone.

00:11:12.625 --> 00:11:14.833
I have only one thing to say.

00:11:15.417 --> 00:11:16.417
Let's win!

00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:19.000
Let's go!

00:11:50.417 --> 00:11:52.167
Commence attack!

00:12:04.458 --> 00:12:05.917
Squad A! Squad C! Switch!

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:09.958
Here it comes! Squad B, block!

00:12:13.042 --> 00:12:15.542
Squad C, keep guarding
and prepare to switch.

00:12:15.542 --> 00:12:16.625
Now!

00:12:16.625 --> 00:12:18.458
As you fall back, prepare
to attack from the side!

00:12:18.958 --> 00:12:21.625
Squads D, E, and F, keep
the sentinels off us!

00:12:22.167 --> 00:12:23.167
Roger!

00:12:24.917 --> 00:12:26.542
Switch!

00:12:26.542 --> 00:12:27.625
The third one!

00:12:28.250 --> 00:12:30.292
<i>I thought she was a beginner.</i>

00:12:30.292 --> 00:12:32.083
<i>But her dexterity is incredible.</i>

00:12:32.083 --> 00:12:33.958
<i>She's so fast I can't even</i>
<i>see the tip of her sword.</i>

00:12:39.292 --> 00:12:40.292
Good job.

00:12:57.042 --> 00:12:59.542
Looks like that information was right...

00:12:59.542 --> 00:13:00.708
Stand back.

00:13:00.708 --> 00:13:02.167
I'll go!

00:13:04.042 --> 00:13:07.250
<i>I thought our plan was to</i>
<i>surround it with the entire group.</i>

00:13:18.542 --> 00:13:19.625
<i>That isn't a Talwar!</i>

00:13:19.625 --> 00:13:20.708
<i>It's a No-Dachi!</i>

00:13:20.708 --> 00:13:22.583
<i>It's not the same as the beta test!</i>

00:13:23.708 --> 00:13:24.708
It's no good!

00:13:25.125 --> 00:13:27.542
Jump back as fast as you can!

00:13:36.833 --> 00:13:37.833
Diabel!

00:13:42.667 --> 00:13:43.667
Diabel!

00:13:47.833 --> 00:13:49.458
Why did you try to do it alone?

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:55.083
You were...

00:13:55.083 --> 00:13:56.792
...a beta tester, weren't you?

00:13:56.792 --> 00:13:57.792
You know.

00:14:01.500 --> 00:14:05.000
You were after the rare item
from the last attack bonus.

00:14:05.417 --> 00:14:07.958
You were a beta tester too?

00:14:12.750 --> 00:14:14.042
Please...

00:14:14.667 --> 00:14:16.125
Defeat...

00:14:16.125 --> 00:14:18.000
Defeat the boss.

00:14:20.292 --> 00:14:21.958
For everyone...

00:14:27.458 --> 00:14:30.042
<i>When this death game started,</i>

00:14:30.750 --> 00:14:34.917
<i>all I thought about</i>
<i>was my own survival.</i>

00:14:36.417 --> 00:14:38.792
Okay, goodbye, Klein.

00:14:40.042 --> 00:14:44.292
<i>But Diabel... even though</i>
<i>you were a beta tester,</i>

00:14:44.292 --> 00:14:46.958
<i>you never abandoned</i>
<i>the other players.</i>

00:14:46.958 --> 00:14:49.667
<i>You led everyone,</i>
<i>and you fought brilliantly!</i>

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:53.125
<i>You tried to do what I couldn't.</i>

00:15:02.208 --> 00:15:03.208
I'll go too.

00:15:03.917 --> 00:15:05.125
Thanks.

00:15:08.292 --> 00:15:10.583
Use the same sequence
as we did for the sentinels.

00:15:10.583 --> 00:15:11.583
Got it.

00:15:20.375 --> 00:15:21.375
Switch!

00:15:24.833 --> 00:15:25.833
Asuna!

00:15:45.083 --> 00:15:46.083
Here he comes again!

00:15:57.500 --> 00:15:58.625
Crap!

00:16:19.083 --> 00:16:20.625
Go!

00:16:21.042 --> 00:16:23.583
We'll hold him off till you recover!

00:16:24.292 --> 00:16:25.458
You're...

00:16:36.375 --> 00:16:37.375
Watch out!

00:16:40.625 --> 00:16:42.875
I'll get you first!

00:16:46.875 --> 00:16:47.917
Asuna...

00:16:47.917 --> 00:16:50.417
One last attack!
Let's do it together!

00:16:50.958 --> 00:16:51.958
Roger!

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:27.292
W-We did it!

00:17:44.750 --> 00:17:47.292
"Coat of Midnight"

00:17:47.292 --> 00:17:48.958
"Coat of Midnight"
Good work.

00:17:48.958 --> 00:17:50.542
That was splendid swordsmanship.

00:17:50.542 --> 00:17:52.167
Congratulations.

00:17:52.167 --> 00:17:54.250
This victory belongs to you.

00:17:54.875 --> 00:17:55.875
No...

00:18:06.125 --> 00:18:07.167
Why?

00:18:09.750 --> 00:18:14.417
Why... Why did you let Diabel die?

00:18:15.208 --> 00:18:16.583
Let him die?

00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:19.083
Of course!

00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:21.958
You knew what technique
the boss would use!

00:18:22.583 --> 00:18:27.708
If you'd given us that information
up front, he wouldn't have died!

00:18:33.833 --> 00:18:36.583
He must be an ex–beta tester!

00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:39.958
That's how he knew all about
the boss's attack patterns.

00:18:39.958 --> 00:18:41.833
He knew, but he kept it from us!

00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:47.083
There's gotta be others here too,
right? Those beta testers!

00:18:47.083 --> 00:18:48.208
Come out!

00:18:52.042 --> 00:18:54.250
--I'm not.
--Aren't you one?

00:19:02.667 --> 00:19:03.667
<i>This is bad.</i>

00:19:04.125 --> 00:19:05.708
<i>At this rate...</i>

00:19:06.167 --> 00:19:07.833
For everyone...

00:19:16.667 --> 00:19:18.292
Hey, you...

00:19:28.833 --> 00:19:31.417
An ex–beta tester, did you say?

00:19:32.958 --> 00:19:36.917
I wish you wouldn't compare
me to those newbies.

00:19:36.917 --> 00:19:39.208
Wh-What?

00:19:40.250 --> 00:19:45.042
Most of the 1,000 people who won
SAO beta test slots were beginners

00:19:45.042 --> 00:19:48.208
who didn't even know
how to level up.

00:19:49.167 --> 00:19:52.250
Even you guys are better than them.

00:19:54.750 --> 00:19:57.542
But I'm not like those guys.

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:05.125
During the beta test, I made it to higher levels
than anyone else was able to reach.

00:20:05.542 --> 00:20:07.833
The reason I knew about
the boss's sword skills

00:20:07.833 --> 00:20:12.125
was because I fought tons of monsters
with those skills on floors far above us.

00:20:13.250 --> 00:20:15.583
I know lots of other things too.

00:20:15.583 --> 00:20:19.042
Way more than any information broker.

00:20:19.917 --> 00:20:22.125
Wh-What?

00:20:22.125 --> 00:20:24.917
That's... That's way worse
than a beta tester!

00:20:24.917 --> 00:20:27.708
That's cheating! You're a cheater.
That's what you are!

00:20:27.708 --> 00:20:29.750
Yeah, a cheater!

00:20:29.750 --> 00:20:31.000
A beta tester and a cheater...

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:32.458
A beater!

00:20:33.458 --> 00:20:36.500
A beater... that's a good name.

00:20:37.583 --> 00:20:38.875
That's right...

00:20:38.875 --> 00:20:40.958
I am a beater.

00:20:40.958 --> 00:20:44.292
From now on, don't confuse
me with the other testers.

00:20:44.708 --> 00:20:45.583
"Coat of Midnight"

00:21:03.250 --> 00:21:04.417
Wait.

00:21:07.625 --> 00:21:10.917
You called my name when
we were fighting.

00:21:10.917 --> 00:21:12.792
Sorry for being rude.

00:21:13.458 --> 00:21:15.542
Or did I mess up the pronunciation?

00:21:15.875 --> 00:21:17.250
Where did you learn it?

00:21:18.042 --> 00:21:22.875
You can see another HP gauge
below yours around here, right?

00:21:22.875 --> 00:21:25.375
Isn't there something
written below that?

00:21:28.500 --> 00:21:30.292
Kirito...

00:21:30.583 --> 00:21:31.708
Kirito?

00:21:32.250 --> 00:21:33.875
Is that your name?

00:21:34.417 --> 00:21:35.417
Yeah.

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:42.750
Oh, so it was written
there all this time!

00:21:44.292 --> 00:21:46.167
You can become powerful.

00:21:46.167 --> 00:21:50.667
So if someone you trust ever
invites you to join a guild,

00:21:50.667 --> 00:21:52.167
don't turn them down.

00:21:52.167 --> 00:21:55.375
Because there's an absolute limit
to what you can do as a solo player.

00:21:56.125 --> 00:21:57.708
Then what about you?

00:22:01.375 --> 00:22:02.750
"Create"
"Dissolve"
"Invite"

00:22:03.083 --> 00:22:05.333
"Will you disband your party?"

00:22:30.083 --> 00:22:41.542
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.875 --> 00:22:53.417
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.833 --> 00:22:59.375
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.708 --> 00:23:05.167
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.583 --> 00:23:10.583
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.917 --> 00:23:15.875
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:22.667
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.000 --> 00:23:26.625
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.208 --> 00:23:33.958
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.292 --> 00:23:39.750
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.083 --> 00:23:46.250
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.042 --> 00:23:53.067
Next Time: "Red-Nosed Reindeer."
